2024-12-04, **Constraints on dark matter annihilation in the Large Magellanic Cloud from multiple low-frequency radio observations**, Zhanfang Chen et.al., [2412.03163v1](http://arxiv.org/abs/2412.03163v1)

 Low-frequency radio emission from the Large Magellanic Cloud~(LMC) is assumed to be dominated by nonthermal synchrotron radiation from energy loss of energetic $e^+/e^-$ in magnetic field. Two different kinds of sources of $e^+/e^-$, dark matter~(DM) annihilation and cosmic rays~(CR) related to massive stars, are taken into account in this paper. We fit the multiple low-frequency radio observations, from 19.7 MHz to 1.4 GHz, with a double power-law model $S\_{nth} =S\_{DM}( rac {
